  "body": "Hi all,\r\n\r\nAn important task for becoming production ready is preventing the usage of HistoricalStates throughout our repo. Currently, we store every single state to the DB, which is not sustainable in a real environment. Instead, we should have the ability to regenerate states through only storing very few of them since the last finalized epoch. This is a tracking issue so we do not forget this important piece of functionality.",
